CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 4, 1954, pg.1 reads: "Abandoned - A deserted baby, found wrapped in a newspaper, in a garbage can in rear of John J. Gerlach's home at 823 Sandusky Street, on cold last Friday morning, was taken to Allegheny General Hospital and declared in fair condition. Byron Thomas of Sandusky Street told police he discovered the 2 or 3-hour-old female baby when he went to dump his trash around 10 A.M.  Gerlach contacted John T. Seli, a priest at St. Paul Catholic Church, who baptized the child "Suzanne X." - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Nurse holding abandoned infant "Suzanne X" in hospital nursery of Allegheny General Hospital
